        In almost all cases however, we want to deal with more than just a single bit. Our computers typically use fixed sized sets of bits to index instructions and values. The size of these groupings is called the word size. A single set of bits that has that word size is called a word.  While word sizes vary by machine, most modern systems use 32 or 64 bit sized words.

